    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-11-03T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-11-03T11:00:00-05:00" n="239"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d239">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/14283: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-11-03T16:00:00+00:00"
                            >November 3, 1938—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 3—1:18 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1280. (1) The information embodied in your 672, November 2, 3 p.m., was brought
                    to Cadogan’s<note n="60" xml:id="d239fn60">Sir Alexander M. J. Cadogan, British
                        Permanent Under Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs.</note> attention
                    this afternoon.</p>
                <p>(2) He expressed pleasure over this evidence of our interest in the question and
                    stated that it was almost certain that the British Government would desire to
                    instruct Craigie to make similar but separate representations. He thought that
                    he could let us know the Foreign Office’s decision by tomorrow.</p>
                <pb facs="0202" n="198" xml:id="pg_198"/>
                <p>(3) He expressed the hope that Grew would meanwhile hold his hand.</p>
                <p>Copy by mail to Paris.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kennedy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
